div1.p:
Surgeon: b. Amherst, Mass., August 9, 1880; s. David Pearce and

Sarah A. (Dunlap) Penhallow; (Prof. Botany .McGill Univ) ed. Pvt. Sch., Montreal, Can.; Harvard Col.,

B.S. 1902; Med. Sch., M.D. 1906; Delta Upsilon. Licensed, Mass., 1906,

New York 1922, Missouri 1923, District of Columbia 1925; Surg. Interne,

Carney Hosp., E. Boston, Mass., 1906-7; Boston City Hosp., 1907-8;

4th Asst. Visiting Surg., 1909; Res. Surg., E. Boston Relief Station,

1910-1913; Instr. Surg., Tufts Col. Med. Sch., 1910-1911; Asst. Demonstra-

tor Anatomy, 1913-15; practiced Gen. Surg., Boston., 1909-15.

National Guard, Mass. Pvt., Corpl., Segt., Coast Arty.; 1st lieut.,

Capt., M.C., 1900-17. Overseas, Am. Red Cross, 1915; Dir., Unit, Am.

Women's War Hosp., Paignton, Eng.; Asst. Dir., Chief Surg., 1915-1918;

Comdg. Officer, Hosp. Mil. VR 76, Mar.-Sept. 1918; Mobile Operating Team,

San Mihiel, Argonne Offensives; Dir. Field Hosp., Sanitary Train;

Comdg. Officer, Field Hosp.; Regt. Surg., 5th Field Arty.; Div. Sanitary

Inspr., 1st Div.; Acting Div. Surg., 1st Div.; Major, U.S.A., 1917-20;

Chief, Surg. Serv., Camp Meade, Md. Nov. 1919-Sept. 1920. U. S. P. H. S.

Hospital #61, Staten Island, N.Y., Chief, Surg. Serv., 1920; Dist. Off.,

U. S. Veterans' Bu. N.Y.C., 1921, Dist. Med. Officer, Dist. Manager;

U.S.V. Hosp. #35, Chief Surg. Serv., 1922; U.S.V. Hosp #32, Wash., D. C.,

August 1, 1923, Comdg. Officer; Sr. Surg. Reserve, 1923-25. Author:

Text Book of Mil. Surg., 1916 and 2nd Edit. 1918, Oxford Press, London;

Numerous Surg. articles, Med. Jour.; Mem. A.M.A.; Assn. Mil. Surg. U.S.; Mass.

State Med. Society; Fellow, American College of Surgeons; Nat. Geog. Soc.;

Champlain Soc., Can.; Veterans Foreign Wars; Am. Legion; Mil. Order World War;

Mil. Order Foreign Wars; Descendants, Colonial Govs. Clubs: Harvard (St. Louis, Mo.,



-2-

Wash., D.C.); Univ. St. Louis, Mo.; Congressional Country, Wash., D. C.;

Cosmos Club, Wash., D.C. Rep. Ch. of Eng. Res: The Wyoming, Wash., D.C.;

Office: The Farragut, Washington, D. C.
